snippet.textDisplay:
Nice job, that was a tough one, the definition of squalor. I don't know how people can live like that.


About Mitsubishi carpet; I detailed at a Mitsu dealer for several years. I found that a Tornador gun works great to get embedded dirt from the cheap, thin pile carpet fibers. I would start with the drill brush, then Tornador, then the extractor.


Also, did you do anything with the headliner? Most of the cigarette smells get trapped up there. The steamer with a cloth gets 99% of the smell out.
snippet.textOriginal:
Nice job, that was a tough one, the definition of squalor.  I don't know how people can live like that.


About Mitsubishi carpet; I detailed at a Mitsu dealer for several years.  I found that a Tornador gun works great to get embedded dirt from the cheap, thin pile carpet fibers.  I would start with the drill brush, then Tornador, then the extractor.  


Also, did you do anything with the headliner?  Most of the cigarette smells get trapped up there.  The steamer with a cloth gets 99% of the smell out.
